ll about the user</a> on December 14, 2008</cite> </p>\r\n	</li>\r\n\r\n	<li id=\"comment-23238\" class=\"altc\">\r\n	<p>[...] That just about raps up this quick overview. However, I only covered a couple of the many new features and improvements to WordPress Version 2.7 The only way to experience the WordPress 2.7 goodness for yourself is to install it, or either upgrade your exsisting installation. Wanna find out even more before downloading? Then just head on over to here -&gt; <a href=\"http://wordpress.org/development/2008/12/coltrane/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://wordpress.org/development/2008/12/coltrane/</a> [...]</p>\r\n	<p><cite>Pingback from <a href=\"http://blog.stupidpoodles.com/2008/12/wordpress-27-coltrane/\" rel=\"external nofollow\" class=\"url\">∞ Infinite ∞ Resolution » Blog Archive » WordPress 2.7 “Coltrane”</a> on December 14, 2008</cite> </p>\r\n	</li>\r\n\r\n	<li id=\"comment-23239\">\r\n	<p>[...] Upgraded stoopad.com to WordPress 2.7 [...]</p>\r\n	<p><cite>Pingback from <a href=\"http://stoopad.com/2008/12/13/saturday-night-brief-2/\" rel=\"external nofollow\" class=\"url\">Saturday Night Brief - at stoopad.com</a> on December 14, 2008</cite> </p>\r\n	</li>\r\n\r\n	<li id=\"comment-23240\" class=\"altc\">\r\n	<p>[...] WordPress 2.7 “Coltrane” is definitely not a minor update. Had I taken the time to read about this new version I would have known this. RTFM. But hey, I backed up my sites before upgrading — that’s kind of a big deal for me <img src=\"http://wordpress.org/news/wp-includes/images/smilies/icon_smile.gif\" alt=\":)\" class=\"wp-smiley\">  [...]</p>\r\n	<p><cite>Pingback from <a href=\"http://kippentuin.nl/ramblings/2008/12/coltrane-shock/\" rel=\"external nofollow\" class=\"url\">WordPress 2.7 COLTRANE | Ramblings</a> on December 14, 2008</cite> </p>\r\n	</li>\r\n\r\n	<li id=\"comment-23241\">\r\n	<p>[...] oh man!&nbsp; WordPress 2.7 “Coltrane” was well worth the wait!&nbsp; My favourite feature is [...]</p>\r\n	<p><cite>Pingback from