December 20, 2008</cite> </p>\r\n	</li>\r\n\r\n	<li id=\"comment-23394\" class=\"altc\">\r\n	<p>[...] been some time since the last major WordPress release, but version 2.7 is now out and I’ve just finished upgrading my various [...]</p>\r\n	<p><cite>Pingback from <a href=\"http://www.datacircle.org/archives/2008/12/20/now-running-wordpress-27/\" rel=\"external nofollow\" class=\"url\">Now running WordPress 2.7 « Data Circle</a> on December 20, 2008</cite> </p>\r\n	</li>\r\n\r\n	<li id=\"comment-23395\">\r\n	<p>[...] after the official announcement of WordPress 2.7 “Coltrane” availability my blog got powered by it! It took roughly 10 [...]</p>\r\n	<p><cite>Pingback from <a href=\"http://nikolay.com/2008/12/11/this-blog-has-been-coltraned/\" rel=\"external nofollow\" class=\"url\">Nikolay » This Blog Has Been Coltrane’d</a> on December 20, 2008</cite> </p>\r\n	</li>\r\n\r\n	<li id=\"comment-23396\" class=\"altc\">\r\n	<p>[...] looks like WordPress has been updated. Version 2.7 is now out, so I’ll be upgrading to that. Hopefully will get my new Theme sorted soon as [...]</p>\r\n	<p><cite>Pingback from <a href=\"http://www.ippoippo.net/blog/archives/2008-12-20/software-updates-geeky-posting/\" rel=\"external nofollow\" class=\"url\">Ippoippo » Software Updates (Geeky posting)</a> on December 20, 2008</cite> </p>\r\n	</li>\r\n\r\n	<li id=\"comment-23397\">\r\n	<p>[...] ben ik overgegaan op de nieuwe versie van wordpress. Deze versie is weer vele malen beter dan de vorige en heeft als grootste [...]</p>\r\n	<p><cite>Pingback from <a href=\"http://www.pepijnkoning.nl/archief/wordpress-27/\" rel=\"external nofollow\" class=\"url\">Pepijn’s Weblog » Archief » WordPress 2.7</a> on December 20, 2008</cite> </p>\r\n	</li>\r\n\r\n	<li id=\"comment-23398\" class=\"altc\">\r\n	<p>[...] Last week, my friend Manish told me about WP 2.7 and so I went and check it out. I even installed it on one of my blogs. WP 2.7 is simply amazing, sexy and slick. What surprised me even more was that the small WP team worked with about 150 developers within their community to contribute to the code base. Power of open-source and crowdsourcing! Read more of the story here. [...]</p>\r\n	<p><cite>Pingback from <a href=\"http://www.sahilparikh.com/2008/12/wordpress-27-%e2%80%9ccoltrane%e2%80%9d/\" rel=\"external nofollow\" class=\"url\">sahil parikh’s blog » WordPress 2.7 “Coltrane”</a> on December 20, 2008</cite> </p>\r\n	</li>\r\n\r\n	<li id=\"comment-23399\">\r\n	<p>[...] how difficult some people find upgrading web apps which is why I thought this comment on the WordPress blog was interesting: … this may be the last time you ever have to manually upgrade WordPress [...]</p>\r\n	<p><cite>Pingback from <a href=\"http://www.frogcake.net/blog/2008/12/20/wordpress-27\" rel=\"external nofollow\" class=\"url\">frogcake.net » WordPress 2.7</a> on December 20, 2008</cite> </p>\r\n	</li>\r\n\r\n	<li id=\"comment-23400\" class=\"altc\">\r\n	<p>[...] upgrade for this site to 2.7 was Smooth as butter this time! And I hear it is “self-upgrading” from now on – Great [...]</p>\r\n	<p><cite>Pingback from <a href=\"http://www.adir1.com/2008/12/post-100-wordpress-27-and-other-updates/\" rel=\"external nofollow\" class=\"url\">adir1 » Blog Archive » Post 100 – WordPress 2.7 and Other Updates</a> on December 20, 2008</cite> </p>\r\n	</li>\r\n\r\n	<li id=\"comment-23401\">\r\n	<p>[...] interface comme ses nouveautés. Pour faire simple, nous allons donc simplement traduire l’article de présentation officiel par Matt, qui résume l’ensemble de la chose, et donne une vidéo en [...]</p>\r\n	<p><cite>Pingback from <a href=\"http://www.hebergement.tv/blog-web/wordpress-27-%e2%80%9ccoltrane%e2%80%9d-48.html\" rel=\"external nofollow\" class=\"url\">Hebergement .TV » Blog Archive » » WordPress 2.7 - “Coltrane”</a> on December 20, 2008</cite> </p>\r\n	</li>\r\n\r\n	<li id=\"comment-23402\" class=\"altc\">\r\n	<p>[...] WordPress 2.7 has arrived and I’ve updated this blog as soon as I can. The process was quick and painless.&nbsp; I like what they’ve done to the interface, but it does take a litte getting used to. Unfortunately, I couldn’t find the time to post anything after the upgrade. Just look at the date on my previous one. That’s about 3 months without a single post. The only activity this blog has seen since then, is a couple of Russian comments that got through Akismet.  The Holidays are here, so I think new posts are in order. Besides the free time and the guilt at having to pay my webhost for nothing, I have another motivation for resurrecting this blog. In the next few weeks I want to focus on improving my writing skills. Everybody tells me the best way to do that is to practice. I just don’t see myself writing essays in a diary or something. So I plan to use my blog instead. I’m sure the web is filled with people who have nothing better to do than criticize my writing. If you feel like doing so, or you see an error here and there, just drop me a line. I won’t get mad. I’ll even thank you for it. [...]</p>\r\n	<p><cite>Pingback from <a href=\"http://urriza.net/blog/2008/12/wordpress-27-and-writing/\" rel=\"external nofollow\" class=\"url\">WordPress 2.7 and Writing | The Akashic Field Chronicle</a> on December 21, 2008</cite> </p>\r\n	</li>\r\n\r\n	<li id=\"comment-23403\">\r\n	<p>[...] Once again I lead a dangerous life and upgraded WordPress to version 2.7 (”Coltrane”). [...]</p>\r\n	<p><cite>Pingback from <a href=\"http://ilkka.kaikuvuo.com/2008/12/yet-again-dangerous-life-upgrading-wordpress/\" rel=\"external nofollow\" class=\"url\">Yet Again Dangerous Life (Upgrading WordPress) | Ip\'s.</a> on December 21, 2008</cite> </p>\r\n	</li>\r\n\r\n	<li id=\"comment-23404\" class=\"altc\">\r\n	<p>[...] <a href=\"http://wordpress.org/development/2008/12/coltrane/\" rel=\"nofollow\">http://wordpress.org/development/2008/12/coltrane/</a> [...]</p>\r\n	<p><cite>Pingback from <a href=\"http://metanoise.netsons.org/index.php/2008/12/21/upgraded/\" r